1. Definitions.

	a. Adapted Material means material subject to Copyright and Similar Rights
		that is derived from or based upon the Licensed Material and in which the
		Licensed Material is translated, altered, arranged, transformed, or
		otherwise modified in a manner requiring permission under the Copyright
		and Similar Rights held by the Licensor. For purposes of this Public
		License, where the Licensed Material is a musical work, performance, or a
		sound recording, Adapted Material is always produced where the Licensed
		Material is synched in timed relation with a moving image.

	b. Adapter's License means the license You apply to Your Copyright and
		Similar Rights in Your contributions to Adapted Material.

	c. BY-SA Compatible License means a license listed at
		https://creativecommons.org/compatiblelicenses (or as updated by
		Creative Commons) as being essentially equivalent to this Public License
		in terms of allowing downstream sharing under the same terms.

	d. Copyright and Similar Rights means copyright and/or similar rights
		closely related to copyright including, without limitation, performance,
		broadcast, sound recording, and Sui Generis Database Rights, without
		regard to how the rights are labeled or categorized. For purposes of this
		Public License, the rights specified in Section 2(b)(1)-(2) are not
		Copyright and Similar Rights.

	e. Effective Technological Measures means those measures that, in the
		absence of proper authority, may not be circumvented under laws
		fulfilling obligations under Article 11 of the WIPO Copyright Treaty
		adopted on December 20, 1996, and similar international agreements.

	f. Exceptions and Limitations means fair use, fair dealing or any other
		exception or limitation to Copyright and Similar Rights that applies to
		Your use of the Licensed Material.

	g. Licensed Material means the artistic or literary work, database, or
		other material to which the Licensor applied this Public License.

	h. Licensed Rights means the rights granted to You subject to the terms and
		conditions of this Public License, which are limited to all Copyright and
		Similar Rights that apply to Your use of the Licensed Material and that
		the Licensor has authority to license.

	i. Licensor means the individual(s) or entity(ies) that offer(s) the
		Licensed Material under the terms of this Public License.

	j. NonCommercial means not primarily intended for or directed towards
		commercial advantage or monetary compensation. For purposes of this
		definition, the exchange of the Licensed Material for other copyrighted
		works by means of digital file-sharing or electronic peer-to-peer
		distribution does not, by itself, constitute a commercial use.

	k. Share means to provide material to the public by any means or process
		that requires permission under the Licensed Rights, such as reproduction,
		public display, public performance, distribution, dissemination,
		communication, or importation, but does not include licensing or
		assigning any rights to the material.

	l. Sui Generis Database Rights means rights other than copyright resulting
		from Directive 96/9/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of
		11 March 1996 on the legal protection of databases, as amended, and/or
		similar laws protecting the extraction and/or re-utilization of the
		contents of a database.

	m. You means the individual or entity exercising the Licensed Rights under
		this Public License. Your has a corresponding meaning.

2. Scope.

	a. License grant. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Public
		License, the Licensor hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free,
		non-sublicensable, non-exclusive, irrevocable license to exercise the
		Licensed Rights in the Licensed Material to:

		1) reproduce and Share the Licensed Material, in whole or in part, in any
			medium or format; and

		2) produce, reproduce, and Share Adapted Material.

		The above rights may be exercised in all media and formats whether now
		known or later developed, and include the right to make such changes as
		are necessary for the purpose of enabling Adapted Material to function
		in the intended medium.

	b. Exceptions and limitations. For the avoidance of doubt, where Exceptions
		and Limitations apply to Your use, this Public License does not apply
		and You do not need to comply with its terms and conditions.

	c. Termination. This Public License and the rights granted hereunder will
		terminate automatically upon any breach by You of the terms of this
		Public License unless such breach is cured within thirty (30) days of
		receipt of a notice from the Licensor specifying the breach.

	d. License  compatibilities. If You Share Adapted Material, you must do so
		under the same license as this Public License (i.e., BY‑NC‑SA), or a
		BY‑SA Compatible License, unless the Licensor has expressly permitted
		otherwise.

3. License Conditions.

	Your exercise of the Licensed Rights is expressly made subject to the
	following conditions.

	a. Attribution. If You Share the Licensed Material (including in object
		code form) or Adapted Material, You must:

		1) retain the following if it is supplied by the Licensor with the
			Licensed Material: identification of the creator(s) of the Licensed
			Material and any others designated to receive attribution, a copyright
			notice, a notice that refers to this Public License, a disclaimer of
			warranties, and a URI or hyperlink to the Licensed Material to the
			extent reasonably practicable;

		2) indicate if You modified the Licensed Material and reasonably
			identify the modifications; and

		3) indicate the license terms of this Public License and provide a
			URI or hyperlink to the Public License.

		You may satisfy the above conditions in any reasonable manner based on
		the medium, means, and context in which You Share the Licensed Material.
		For example, it may be reasonable to satisfy the conditions by providing
		a link to a location where the required information is available.

	b. NonCommercial. You may not exercise any of the rights granted to You in
		Section 2 above in any manner that is primarily intended for or directed
		toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. If You are unsure
		whether a use is commercial, you must obtain permission from the
		Licensor.

	c. ShareAlike. If You create Adapted Material, You must distribute the
		Adapted Material under the same license as the Licensed Material (i.e.,
		BY‑NC‑SA) or a BY‑SA Compatible License, unless the Licensor has
		expressly permitted otherwise. You may satisfy this condition by
		applying the same license to the Adapted Material and including a
		statement that the Adapted Material is offered under that license.

4. Sui Generis Database Rights.

	Where the Licensed Rights include Sui Generis Database Rights that apply to
